resources.string: Get notifications if you were possibly exposed to someone with COVID-19.
Permissions needed to install and optimally use this app
Continuation of permissions needed to install and optimally use this app

Turn on Exposure Notifications so that %1$s can notify you if you've been near someone who has reported having COVID-19. 

Your phone uses Bluetooth to securely collect and share random IDs with other phones that are nearby. 

The date, duration and signal strength associated with an exposure will be shared with the app.

Share app usage and performance data with Google
To help maintain and improve the app, some limited de-identified data about app performance and usage is shared with Google. This data does not identify you. %1$s

Protect your community and share your COVID-19 test result
Sharing your COVID-19 test result, especially if you have tested positive, will help notify others who may have been exposed. It will also let others in your community monitor for symptoms.
Your app isn\'t currently checking for possible exposures. To be notified of possible COVID-19 exposure, turn on Exposure Notifications.
